Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt:
Defendant Nicole A Wetzel in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Defendant Nicole A Wetzel in custody.  Jennifer Lynn Williams appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by state, defense and defendant.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 60 MONTHS consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 13 DAYS time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 30 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 30 MONTHS.  Conditions of extended supervision:
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with recommended treatment.
*Mental health assesment  and comply with recommended treatment.
*Random urine screens.
*Absolute sobriety. No drugs or alcohol
*No contact with co-actor: Abimael Trevino
*No unsupervised contact with N.T.
*Seek and maintain fulltime employment
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy
*Vocational/educational training
*Parenting classes
*Comply with Child Protective Services regulations
*Pay all costs and surcharges

Court ordered defendant to provide DNA sample and imposed mandatory surcharges.
The Court ordered the defendant to pay DNA surcharge AND all other applicable costs and any other surcharges and assessments to be collected by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and to convert to civil judgment upon release to extended supervision but remain a condition of extended supervision.  

State informs court there is no request for restitution.

Court informs defendant he is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program or Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may not possess any firearms and that he may not vote until civil rights are restored.
Court ordered defendant REMANDED into to the custody of the MIlwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
